Find two lines such that together with the x-axis, they form a container that holds the maximum amount of water.

height = [1,8,6,2,5,4,8,3,7]
Explanation:
Choose two indices i and j
The height is limited by the shorter line
Width = distance between them

Solution 1:
Brute force approach:
fun main() {
	val nums = intArrayOf(1,8,6,2,5,4,8,3,7)
   	var maxWater = 0
    // 1. find all possible containers
    for(i in nums.indices){
        for(j in i+1 until nums.size){ // initialises with i+1 because i itself is not a container
            val width = j - i // width between the left and right boundary
            val height = minOf(nums[i],nums[j]) // pick minimum height 
            val area = width * height
            
            maxWater = maxOf(maxWater,area)
        }
    }
    print(maxWater)
}

Solution 2: Optimal Solution
class Solution {
    fun maxArea(height: IntArray): Int {
        var maxWater = 0
        var i = 0
        var j = height.size - 1
        while(i < j){
            val w = j - i
            var h = 0
            if(height[i] < height[j]){
                h = height[i]
                i++
            }else{
                h = height[j]
                j--
            }
            val area = w * h
            maxWater = maxOf(maxWater,area)
        }
        return maxWater
    }
}
